comment.body:
> @damsfx I understand this fixes the error, but shouldn't we keep Laravel behavior and fix the code that fetches the Currency from the Session to use the ISO format instead?

That would certainly be a much better solution.  
@tobias-kuendig  any thoughts on this?

comment.diff_hunk:
@@ -87,7 +87,11 @@ public function onRun()
         /** @var Collection<Wishlist>|Wishlist[] items */
         /** @var Wishlist currentItem */
         $this->items       = $this->getWishlists();
-        $this->currentItem = $this->items->first();
+        $this->currentItem = $this->items->find($this->decode($this->param('id')));
+
+        if (! $this->currentItem) {
+            $this->currentItem = $this->items->first();
+        }

